<title>POLAND: Polish KGHM buys anhydrite mine for PLN 6.5 mln.</title>
<headline>Polish KGHM buys anhydrite mine for PLN 6.5 mln.</headline>
<dateline>WARSAW 1996-09-26</dateline>
<text>
<p>Polish KGHM copper concern's investment subsidiary Dolnoslaska Spolka Inwestycyjna SA (DSI) bought on Thursday 75 percent of the Nowy Lad Ltd anhydrite mine for 6.56 million zlotys, the privatisation ministry said.</p>
<p>It said in a statement 20 percent of shares would be offered to the mine's employees and five percent retained by the privatisation ministry for reprivatisation claims.</p>
<p>KGHM's DSI also agreed to raise the mine's capital by a 5.3 million for investment purposes and increase wages for two years running by 25 percent above the price growth index.</p>
<p>-- Warsaw Newsroom +48 22 653 9700</p>
